  "body": "I'm working on rebasing OpenShift on top of Kubernetes 1.6 and I just noticed that if you try to exec/attach to a pod, the CRI protobuf messages for AttachRequest and ExecRequest only allow you to specify stdin and tty. You are not able to specify stdout or stderr. The handlers for serving exec and attach streaming requests force stdout to true, and stderr to true when not using a tty. Is there a reason that stdout and stderr are hard-coded and not optional?\r\n\r\nI'm able to work around this by saying I \"want\" stdout and stderr, and sending their data to `ioutil.Discard`, but I don't think that's a good long-term solution. I believe this is a regression and we should restore the ability to selectively enable both stdout and stderr.\r\n\r\nThoughts?\r\n\r\n@yujuhong @dchen1107 @vishh @Random-Liu @timstclair @smarterclayton @derekwaynecarr @liggitt @sttts @kubernetes/sig-node-bugs ",
